memory: I bought this along with three of my best friends on our Spring Break trip to Chicago last year.
I also have the same beanie in pink.
You can never go wrong with a basic black beanie. This keeps my head warm in the winter time.
I also have this beanie in maroon.
I also have this beanie in olive green.
This is my favorite hat. I wear it all the time, especially when I am dancing because it makes me feel confident.
I attended Stony Brook University for my first year of college, and then I transferred to Parsons. I always wear this when I find myself missing it.
I wore this hat as uniform when I worked part time at Boba Guys last summer.
I just really like this color and I really like Adidas.
Moxie is an all girls urban hip hop dance group that consists of some of my close friends from my old university. I really look up to them when it comes to confidence.
This hat has been in the family coat closet for the longest time and I remember seeing it in there all the time growing up. I wore it to a Yankee game for Fourth of July.
This hat reminds me of Long Island and suburbia, which is where I grew up.
I wore this to the beach everyday when I was in Martinique. It reminds me of summertime.
I love this shade of pink.
Someone gifted this as a gag gift at my brother's workplace, but no one was going to actually wear it. So I took it as a good reminder.
I love Odd Future's music and I wore this when I made a dance concept video with my two friends.
A healthy reminder to myself on self worth.
One of my favorite tees that I own. The color makes me happy and reminds me of sunny days.
I liked the other Stussy tee so much I wanted to get it in purple. It's hand-dyed so there isn't another t-shirt like it.
I used to train for dance at Sandbox almost every single week last year. My friend James who started the company gave me one of the shirts for my 21st birthday.
SAYAW is an annual dance competition held by I participated during my freshman year of college and got to take workshops from choreographers that I look up to from the West Coast.
I bought this on Black Friday sale when I was in high school with friends. It's a XL in Mens so its huge on me. I love the graphic design of the roses.
I wore this on a first date in Port Jefferson, Long Island. I remember eating ice cream and walking along the water with my boyfriend at the time.
I bought this at the Mura Masa concert a year ago at Terminal 5. I love his music and it was such a fun show.
My room mate gave this to me last summer because she wasn't going to wear it anymore. I wore it in Martinique and it reminds me of the nice weather there.
I always wear this top for a night out. It makes me feel good and I can pair it with anything.
I wore this on my 19th birthday when I was at Stony Brook and celebrated with close friends. I love the way it accentuates my shoulders.
This is my only real "formal" dress shirt. I wear it for professional interviews, career fairs, etc. I think I got a makeup stain on it though...
I bought this on my recent spring break trip to LA. It's probably the most expensive shirt I have so far. I love the gold detailing, and I like Drake, who created the line.
The airbnb I stayed at was right next to this streetwear store. It reminds me of my visit to Chicago.
I bought this from the STEADY pop up store when I interned for them. It's a mens XL but I like how comfortable it is and the boldness of the red.
I got this flannel for $6 and reminds me of when I went to Washington Square Park for a picnic last year.
I bought this when I was hanging out with my Stony Brook friends during freshman winter break. It was one of my first streetwear purchases.
I thrifted this after a dance shoot with my two friends, James and Alex. Pink is my favorite color if you can't tell by now.
My friends at Stony Brook bought me this for my 19th birthday. It always comes in handy when it rains.
My mom bought this jacket for me a few years ago. Sadly there is one button missing on the pocket so I can't close it.
I bought this after I recieved my paycheck at Boba Guys last August. It's my favorite jacket so far and I love the detailing.
I bought this at L Train Vintage, a thrift store in East Village for only $8.
I got this at a nightmarket in Taipei a few years ago. It's my favorite winter coat and I wear it all the time.
An old jean jacket that was my moms. My actual favorite denim jacket got stolen at Fat Buddha on my 21st birthday, so I now wear this one instead.
I love how oversized this coat is. I would always wear it to art museums.
I've been wearing this jacket a lot recently. It's perfect for the spring weather, and I wore it a lot over spring break in Los Angeles.
This dress reminds me of the summer time. I wore it to my Ethereal Asian American art exhibit where I showcased my photography.
I really love the way this dress fits on me. I wore it out when I was in LA with my friends, to a gay club called Flaming Saddles... It was an interesting experience.
I thrifted this last year in Chicago during spring break with my friends. I got it for $8, but I still have not worn it since no formal events have come up.
I wore this to ASA formal at Stony Brook, where I performed with my best friend Irving. I sang and played the ukulele.
I feel like a farmer whenever I wear this, but in a good way?
I got this on sale, but had to get it tailored because I am so short. The zipper in the back is broken and doesn't go up all the way.
I wore this to a nice restaurant last summer in NYC with my two friends, then passed out in Times Square right after. Not a great look.
This turtleneck pairs so well with everything, but I'm sad that I somehow I got a huge stain on it.

I bought this at the Elements Dance Competition hosted by Boston University during my freshman year, where I also learned from choreographers from the West Coast. It was such a great experience; I wish I could attend again.
This reminds me of my older brother because he gave it to me before he moved to Los Angeles around a month ago.
I got this at a streetwear thrift store during my recent spring break trip to LA. I love the colors and how oversized it is on me.
I got this as a gift from my boss at my internship with STEADY, during their opening reception of their pop up shop.
This is my favorite crewneck that I own. I love the colors and I bought it during the winter break when I was still at Stony Brook, with my friends at the time.
I almost transferred to USC, which was my dream college in high school. I bought this when I was visiting LA for the first time.
I really like the logo detailing on the back. This sweater is just very comfortable and one of my favorite sweaters I own.
I got this during a Black Friday sale in high school with my friends at the mall.  It's one of my most thick sweatshirts and I like how it is so baggy.
I thrifted this on Melrose Ave when I was in LA. The ruffled sleeves makes me feel so fancy, even though I got it for $7.
This sweater makes me feel really confident because it's off the shoulder and I love the sleeves. I wear it a lot in the winter.
I used to volunteer for Tzu Chi, a Buddhist charity organization all throughout middle and high school. I stopped volunteering after I went to college, but I really want to get back into it.
I took this cardigan from my dad so it's huge on me. I used to wear it all the time in high school. The ends of the sleeves are starting to unravel.
Honestly these are pretty uncomfortable to wear. I feel like I can't breathe in them.
I bought these off of an app and they are my most favorite pair of jeans I own. I wear them all the time and I've had them since high school.
I got these on sale and wear them all the time during the winter. They pair with almost everything I own.
I wear these pretty much all the time. They are the most comfortable pair of sweats I own, and I dance a lot in them too. They were a staple when I was at Stony Brook.

These are one of the oldest pairs of pants that I own in my closet. I've been wearing them since the beginning of high school. They are so comfortable and I love wearing them to bum around or dance in.
These pants remind me of Kim Possible, who is who I dressed up as for Hallloween when I visited my friend at Cornell. The hook kept falling off so I had to sew it back on.
I call these my power pants because the combination of the style and color makes me feel so confident. I wear these when I want to feel good and when I have job interviews.
I love the baggy fit of these pants and wore them on my 21st birthday celebration. These are definetely my favorite pair of pants that I own in my closet so far.
The fabric of these pants is very light and airy so I love wearing them in the summer time. I got them at a nightmarket in Taiwan a few years ago.

One of my favorite pair of pants in my closet. I bought them in Taiwan when I taught English in the countryside because we weren't allowed to wear shorts. One end of the drawstrings is missing because it got caught in the
My favorite pair of shorts. I wear them all the time in the summer and they fit me perfectly.
Another item of clothing my room mate gave to me over the summer. I wore them when I hung out with my old room mates from Stony Brook for a birthday party.
I wore this a lot when I was in Martinique. I have to roll them up because they are long and then the pockets always show. They remind me of the beach.
Purchased at a nightmarket, I wear these the most often when I go to dance workshops in the summertime.
I got these in summer of 2014. I wore them for 3 years almost everywhere I went, including places like Taiwan, Spain, and LA.
These are my favorite pair of shoes so far. They are so comfortable and they make me feel confident when I dance.
I bought these sneakers with my first ever paycheck when I shot for Nike Air Society; my first professional photography gig.
My main pair of sneakers when I dance. I wear them so often that there's a small hole forming.
The platform of these sneakers make me feel tall, but they are actually quite uncomfortable to walk around for a while in.
I remember finding these senior year of high school and feeling so excited since I got them for cheap. I had wanted a pair for a while but they were originally too expensive.
My brother bought these for me for my birthday a few years ago. They are my favorite pair of boots to wear in the winter time and have clearly been through a lot.
I wore these during tailgate during my freshman year of college and threw up all over them because I got too drunk. They were brand new too... I'm not proud.
My mom bought these for me on her trip to Greece. They are handmade and very comfortable to walk in. I love going to the beach wearing these. They remind me of going on vacation and the summertime.
I wear these when I go out. They make me feel tall and confident, and they are surprisingly pretty comfortable to walk in.
I use this backpack a lot, especially when I am traveling. I bought this in Sweden because I thought it would be cheaper since the brand originated from there, but it was actually more expensive.
This is the current backpack that I use. It fits so many things inside and is waterproof. The color reminds me of the sky.
I can fit so many things in this backpack and it will still feel light. I used to use this backpack when I was a student at Stony Brook.
Are you really a Parsons student if you don't own this?
I use this everytime I have to stay somewhere overnight for a day or two.
I got this for free at the CD event last semester. The colors remind me of IKEA.
This bag is perfect for when I want to sneak snacks into the movie theater, also when I want to use a nicer bag to put my camera in.
I rarely use this purse, but when I do, it's for special occasions. I can only fit my phone in it.
I never knew how convenient and lifechanging a fanny pack was before I bought this. I wore it to a Brockhampton concert a few months ago.
What I use to carry my DSLR camera in. I use this when I am traveling and pretty much everywhere I go when I'm taking photos.
One of my most closest and best friends, Casey made this scarf for me. It's one of the most thoughtful gifts I've received.
This is probably the oldest item I still have in my closet. It was given to me when I was in the sixth grade at Chinese School for Secret Santa. I still wear it all the time.
From a collaboration between The Hundreds and Christina Paik, who is my favorite photographer and one of my biggest inspirations for why I transferred to Parsons.
I also have this in black.
